{
  "name": "Evolution WhatsApp RAG Calendar Agent",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "Configura este workflow antes de activarlo:\n\n1. Asigna credenciales a `OpenAI Chat Model` y `Embeddings OpenAI`.\n\n2. En `OpenAI Chat Model` selecciona un modelo con function calling (recomendado: `gpt-4o-mini`). Modelos sin tool calling provocarán bucles y error de max iterations.\n\n3. Asigna credenciales PostgreSQL al nodo `RAG Company Knowledge` con host `postgres`, puerto `5432`, base `rag`.\n\n4. Edita el nodo `Normalize Evolution Message` para poner tu `evolutionApiKey` real y el `instanceName` de tu instancia de Evolution.\n\n5. El nodo `MCP Tool` conecta al `MCP Server Trigger` del propio workflow. Todas las herramientas del agente (`RAG Company Knowledge` y los nodos de Google Calendar) se enrutan por ahí: actívalos cuando los necesites y conéctalos al `MCP Server Trigger` con `ai_tool`.\n\n6. En Evolution configura el webhook de entrada hacia la URL de producción de este workflow.\n\nEste flujo está pensado para mensajes entrantes de WhatsApp, agrupa mensajes recibidos en una ventana de 5 segundos y solo deja continuar a la última ejecución.",
        "height": 350,
        "width": 493,
        "color": 7
      },
      "id": "d0848047-9bc5-432f-aec5-8b110babb17e",
      "name": "Notas de Setup",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        560,
        1136
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "El agente usa dos capas de contexto:\n\n- Redis Buffer: agrupa varios mensajes seguidos en 5 segundos\n- Simple Memory (buffer en memoria de n8n): mantiene el historial de los últimos turnos\n\nEl RAG va como herramienta de consulta y Google Calendar entra por MCP Tool para crear, consultar, modificar y cancelar citas.",
        "height": 260,
        "width": 401,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "c834fd1c-60d2-4a72-a908-803aec86c047",
      "name": "Notas de Arquitectura",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        2192,
        1232
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "evolution-whatsapp-agent",
        "options": {
          "responseData": "ok"
        }
      },
      "id": "1008f18e-5b23-417f-9f17-4a3fe25d83ea",
      "name": "Evolution Incoming Webhook",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        -176,
        1552
      ],
      "webhookId": "evolution-whatsapp-agent"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "jsCode": "const body = $json.body ?? $json;\nconst data = body.data ?? body;\nconst key = data.key ?? {};\nconst message = data.message ?? {};\nconst fromMe = key.fromMe ?? data.fromMe ?? false;\nconst remoteJid = key.remoteJid ?? data.remoteJid ?? data.from ?? body.sender ?? '';\nconst text = message.conversation ?? message.extendedTextMessage?.text ?? message.imageMessage?.caption ?? message.videoMessage?.caption ?? data.body ?? body.body ?? '';\nif (fromMe || !remoteJid || !text) {\n  return null;\n}\nconst messageId = key.id ?? data.id ?? `${Date.now()}`;\nconst instanceName = body.instance ?? body.instanceName ?? data.instance ?? 'CHANGE_ME';\nconst sessionId = remoteJid.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9:_-]/g, '_');\nconst pushName = data.pushName ?? body.pushName ?? '';\nconst webhookItem = $('Evolution Incoming Webhook').first().json;\nconst evolutionApiKey = webhookItem.body?.apikey ?? webhookItem.apikey ?? body.apikey ?? data.apikey ?? '';\nreturn {\n  json: {\n    rawBody: body,\n    remoteJid,\n    pushName,\n    text,\n    chatInput: text,\n    messageId,\n    instanceName,\n    sessionId,\n    memorySessionId: `wa-memory:${sessionId}`,\n    bufferKey: `wa-buffer:${sessionId}`,\n    evolutionBaseUrl: 'http://evolution-api:8080',\n    evolutionApiKey,\n    googleCalendarMcpUrl: 'http://host.docker.internal:3001/mcp'\n  }\n};"
      },
      "id": "26ee7a19-6f09-47e6-a73a-10bc6f147f4c",
      "name": "Normalize Evolution Message",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        64,
        1552
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "get",
        "propertyName": "bufferSnapshot",
        "key": "={{ $json.bufferKey }}",
        "keyType": "string",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "afc4cc3b-d4ef-4dc3-9cac-8ace08273b6e",
      "name": "Get Buffer Snapshot",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.redis",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        288,
        1552
      ],
      "credentials": {
        "redis": {
          "id": "Myw5B5gIEfw2xhVS",
          "name": "Redis account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "jsCode": "const norm = $('Normalize Evolution Message').first().json;\nlet previous = null;\ntry {\n  previous = $json.bufferSnapshot ? JSON.parse($json.bufferSnapshot) : null;\n} catch (error) {\n  previous = null;\n}\nconst now = Date.now();\nconst withinWindow = previous && Number(previous.updatedAt || 0) >= now - 5000;\nconst mergedText = [withinWindow ? previous.text : '', norm.text].filter(Boolean).join('\\n');\nconst debounceToken = `${norm.messageId}:${now}`;\nconst payload = {\n  token: debounceToken,\n  text: mergedText,\n  updatedAt: now,\n  remoteJid: norm.remoteJid,\n  pushName: norm.pushName,\n  instanceName: norm.instanceName\n};\nreturn {\n  json: {\n    ...norm,\n    chatInput: mergedText,\n    debounceToken,\n    bufferPayload: JSON.stringify(payload)\n  }\n};"
      },
